dataElements.name: Skin_Cl_Lesion_Papilloma_T
dataElements.description:
A papilloma is a single or multiple yellow bumps on the skin. For children who live in endemic villages, this may be the early presentation of yaws.
Tick this box if the patient presents papilloma(s).

translations.value: Lésion surélevée jaunâtre sur la peau. Il peut y avoir un seul ou plusieurs papillomes. Pour les enfants vivant dans des villages d’endémie, il peut être le premier signe du pian.

dataElements.name: Skin_Cl_Lesion_Ulcer_T
dataElements.description:
An ulcer is a painless skin lesion characterized by a necrotic center, undermined edges and oedematous skin. An early ulcerative lesion has a diameter of less than 2 cm and a late ulcerative lesion has a diameter of more than 2 cm. 
Tick this box if the patient presents ulcer(s).

dataElements.description: An imported case is defined as a case that has most probably been infected in another country. Please tick "Yes" if this is the case.

dataElements.name: Skin_Cl_Lesion_Nodule_T
dataElements.description:
A nodule is a lesion that extends from the skin into the subcutaneous tissue. It is 1–2 cm in diameter. It is usually painless but may be itchy and the surrounding skin may be discoloured compared to adjacent areas.
Tick this box if the patient presents a nodule.

dataElements.name: GEN_Tx_adverseEvent_specify_T
dataElements.description: A serious adverse event (SAE) is defined as any untoward medical occurrence that at any dose: results in death; is life-threatening; requires inpatient hospitalization or causes prolongation of existing; hospitalization; results in persistent or significant disability/incapacity; is a congenital anomaly/birth defect, or requires intervention to prevent permanent impairment or damage.

dataElements.name: Skin_Cl_Lesion_Vesicle_T
dataElements.description: Tick this box if the patient presents vesicle(s).

dataElements.name: CL_Classif_T
dataElements.description: Situation I :  <4 lesion(s);  <4 cm in diam.; not potentially disfiguring; infected with L. major; not immunocompromised / Situation II : <4 lesion(s); <4 cm in diam.; locally treatable;  infected with L. infantum  or L. tropica; not immunocompromised / ? 4 lesions; ? 4 cm in diam.; not compatible with local treatment; immunocompromised or suffering from unbalanced diabetes.

dataElements.name: Skin_Cl_Lesion_Papule_T
dataElements.description:
A papule is defined as a painless, raised skin lesion, less than 1 cm in diameter. The surrounding skin is reddened.
Tick this box if the patient presents papule(s).

dataElements.name: Skin_Cl_Lesion_Plaque_T
dataElements.description:
A plaque is a firm, painless, elevated, well-demarcated lesion more than 2 cm in diameter with irregular edges. The skin over the lesion is often reddened or otherwise discolored. 
Tick this box if the patient presents plaque(s).

dataElements.description:
An oedema is a diffuse, extensive, non-pitting, ill defined margin, firm, and may be painful with or without color change over the affected skin. 
Tick this box if the patient presents oedema.
